When deleting a permission, it takes you to a confirmation page which currently says:  Are you sure you want to delete Project Role (X) for premission: Y.  It would be helpful if this page also provided the reminder that the permission scheme is shared by multiple projects.  Since this is a different page altogether, it is easy to forget that the changes you are making applies to more projects than just the one you are altering it for.  I made the mistake today of modifying permission scheme for one project, but it affected 20 projects.  I had to go back and put everything back the way it was, then copy the scheme, then modify it.  This warning would have saved me a lot of work.

