Presented in user story form:

{quote}
As a JIRA administrator,
I want a way to programmatically manage permission schemes,
because manually setting for 40+ permissions, and then quadruple checking to make sure I got it right, is a sadness that lingers for the rest of my days administering JIRA
{quote}

The deprecated SOAP API does provide [functionality for managing permission mappings|https://docs.atlassian.com/rpc-jira-plugin/latest/com/atlassian/jira/rpc/soap/beans/RemotePermissionMapping.html], however it can only assign permissions to [Users and Groups|https://docs.atlassian.com/rpc-jira-plugin/latest/com/atlassian/jira/rpc/soap/beans/RemoteEntity.html]. The lack of support for assigning permissions to Roles makes the SOAP API less than useful for managing permissions on modern JIRA instances.

With updated API support, I could automate the creation and enforcement of permission schemes using a configuration management tool such as Puppet or Chef. Less manual editing and associated mistakes.

